description:
&lt;p&gt;MRI Radiographer | Imaging | Manchester | Bank | Band 5/ 6 Equivalent&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Spire Manchester has an exciting opportunity for a highly motivated MRI Radiographer to join our outstanding Imaging Department.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Spire Manchester Hospital is a brand new, £65m state-of-the-art healthcare facility offering patients a wide range of integrated surgical, medical and diagnostic services. The rapidly expanding team in Manchester consists of over 500 colleagues, who thrive in the welcoming atmosphere that is friendly, supportive and progressive. We are also proud to say our hospital was awarded ‘Outstanding’ status in our 2019 CQC report.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Duties and responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll work collaboratively to deliver a high quality, professional radiographic service with a focus on MRI and general radiography. You will adapt to new technologies and clinical developments, being responsible for making sound, considered judgements and informed decisions on theimaging required and then provide highly skilled and specialised imaging for patients. Team working is a big part of this role, so successful working relationships with our Nurses, Physiotherapists and expert Consultants will be a defining factor in delivering the outstanding patient care we are proud of.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are looking for&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;HCPC registration and Radiography degree&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Specialist practice in MRI&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You should be innovative, highly motivated and possess good communication skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer employees a competitive salary&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Save an average of £50 per month with our free onsite car park&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;On-Site Gym&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please see the attached benefits leaflet under ‘’additional information’’ for more details. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We commit to our employees well-being through work life balance, on-going development, support and reward.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Spire Healthcare is a leading independent hospital group that has been putting patients at the heart of everything we do for over 40 years. We have 39 hospitals, 10 clinics and a Specialist Cancer Care Centre across England, Wales and Scotland.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information about this role or for an informal conversation about the range of career options available with Spire please contact Claire Murphy on 07921067195 or claire.murphy@spirehealthcare.com&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;For us, &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;it&#39;s more than just treating patients; it&#39;s about looking after people. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
